geneSummary: PIK3CA, the catalytic subunit of PI3-kinase, is frequently mutated in a diverse range of cancers including breast, endometrial and cervical cancers.

mutationEffect.description: The PIK3CA E726K mutation is located between the accessory and the kinase domains of the protein. There is conflicting functional data for this mutation. Expression of this mutation in Ba/F3 but not MCF10A cell lines led to proliferation in the absence of growth factors (PMID: 29533785).

variantSummary: There is conflicting and/or weak data describing the biological significance of the PIK3CA E726K mutation.
